article.description: North Carolina Central tops Savannah State 62-49
article.headline: North Carolina Central tops Savannah State 62-49
article.linkText: North Carolina Central tops Savannah State 62-49
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. -- Nimrod Hilliard led four in double figures with 15 points and North Carolina Central topped Savannah State 62-49 on Monday. The Eagles face in-state rival N.C. A&T on Thursday with a chance to complete an undefeated season in the Mid-Eastern Conference. North Carolina Central (23-6, 15-0) went on a 13-2 run early -- including back-to-back 3-pointers by Anthony McDonald -- and had a six-point spurt a little later to lead 33-25 at the break. An 11-2 run at the start of the second half, including another 3 by McDonald, pushed the lead to 44-27. Another 11-point spurt a few moments later made it a 20-point game. Savannah State responded with a nine-point run -- capped by Alante Fenner's 3-pointer -- to cut the deficit to 11 at 54-43 with 4:51 left, but the Tigers only made two more baskets down the stretch. Savannah State (9-20, 5-10) was led by Fenner with 11 points.
